reviews.reviewText: For the most part it was easy to assemble. But not all the pieces screwed in well. Feel like it is a bit flimsy. We made it work and it looks great and matches our theme. Overall I am happy with the purchase.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 23, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect for small spaces
reviews.reviewText: I love the way this looks for the price point. It’s perfect for a small angled wall in our hallway, that helps add a little storage space to our home that is lacking cabinets. Fits a bunch of kids towels/washclothes, a dozen boxes of tissues/toilet paper, and some cute Knick knacks in the open shelves for style.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Lowest quality “furniture” I’ve ever seen
reviews.reviewText: I will start off by saying I am very handy. This is not to brag. This is for context so you know where I’m coming from. I’ve installed flooring, tile backsplashes, baseboards, light fixtures, bifold doors, faucets, the list goes on and on. I use a lot of power tools. I am a very hardcore DIYer, in other words, and am perfectly willing to pour extensive time and effort into projects.I am returning this because I cannot make it work without hours of effort and extra materials. Every hole is misplaced, missing, or too large (the dowels and screws flop around). I can’t drill new holes because they’d need to overlap with the existing ones and would compromise the MDF (would probably split it). To make this work, I would need to use wood putty, construction adhesive, and more. It is also the worst quality MDF I’ve ever seen. Infinitely worst than even the Target Room Essentials cheapo cubby storage units (not the nicer Threshold ones!). If this was $30 I might be willing to take some time and “hack” it, but this was $90+. My expectations were low and this didn’t even come close to meeting them.Returning this type of item is a total pain but it’s still a much better option than keeping this piece of garbage.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 22, 2023

reviews.reviewText: I’m shocked at how simple this was to assemble. It’s really sturdy considering how cheap it was. I usually hate putting things like this together but this was an absolute breeze. Took me about an hour. Looks exactly as pictured.

reviews.reviewText: Great for small spaces like my mudroom. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 12, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Perfect for small bathroom
reviews.reviewText: This cabinet is exactly what I needed for a little bit of extra storage in our master bathroom. It may not be fine furniture (think Ikea quality), but once assembled it's quite sturdy and the perfect size for a small bathroom. It was a little challenging to assemble, but the size and neutral color are just what I was looking for.
